{"author":{"id":"c4712575109c327bdd55aba22ffc85056a57c52d1f733268a7aaae0da808160e"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1517337260,"nonce":"YJ8j/dzevP73R3sSodusJvRcexg=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUyOTI4OTEwNTg=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1696","origin":"github"},"title":"HOMER should be a Galaxy tool provided by the IUC","message":"[HOMER](http://homer.ucsd.edu/homer/) is a tool widely used for ChIP-seq (and other NGS) data analysis. \n\nThere are two HOMER tools on Galaxy: \n- [`homer` by keyvin](https://toolshed.g2.bx.psu.edu/repository?repository_id=aaa8f7315ce6dac2\u0026changeset_revision=74c1fc7bb164) which, if I'm reading correctly, hasn't been updated since 2012, despite HOMER's relatively frequent enhancements (most recent release was a week ago, of v4.9).\n- [`homer_47` by chseward](https://toolshed.g2.bx.psu.edu/repository?repository_id=d64d9630d122a665\u0026changeset_revision=9764a14c8e3a) which is meant to implement homer version 4.7 (relatively recent) but fails to install. \n\nGalaxy would benefit a great deal from a reference implementation of a HOMER galaxy tool. \n\ncc @bwassie, @bgruening","files":null}]}